The paper deals with image orientation detection, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses deep learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates its model on different public datasets, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
